						<div class="postbody">So yeah, I might be making a NES version of Chu Chu Rocket at some time.  I've calculated that you can get all possibilities of mice entering and leaving squares, as well as different wall positions, within 256 tiles per scanline.
<br />The big question is how to iterate over a map and calculate new values for mice on the map, can it be done within 16 frames?</div>

					
